ul.li: proc_release: Implemented by single_release (frees seq_file allocation)
Memory Limit: If output > 4096B, seq_read loops back to start/show with updated offset to fill multiple read() requests.

div.p: Process calls open("/proc/mydevice"). Kernel invokes mydev_proc_open.
single_open allocates the iterator. m->op is set to the single-record helper.
seq_read invokes start(). Since it's single_open, it returns a dummy pointer.
mydev_proc_show executes. seq_printf writes human-readable stats.
Kernel transfers formatted text to the userspace address provided.
